00:14.005 --> 00:15.211
Lucille.

00:15.212 --> 00:16.648
Hey!

00:16.736 --> 00:18.066
Hey, it's looking good.

00:18.100 --> 00:20.068
- Tell me you got good news.
- I do.

00:20.102 --> 00:22.333
Stable Shelters' bridge loan
has just been approved.

00:22.367 --> 00:24.002
Harvey pulled
some strings at the bank.

00:24.036 --> 00:26.108
Ah, good to see you,
Harvey.

00:26.142 --> 00:27.914
I figured you was allergic
to manual labor.

00:27.948 --> 00:30.719
Oh, I'll get my hands dirty
if I have to, Lucille.

00:30.753 --> 00:33.027
But I believe
charity begins at home.

00:33.061 --> 00:34.928
Yeah, and based on
that Rolex you wear,

00:34.963 --> 00:37.035
I'd say that your favorite cause
is doing pretty good.

00:37.069 --> 00:39.271
We're gonna need
your signature here.

00:39.305 --> 00:41.807
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
15% interest?

00:41.842 --> 00:44.176
They're worried about
Stable Shelter's solvency.

00:44.210 --> 00:45.343
They're worried?

00:45.378 --> 00:47.045
They should try being
executive director.

00:47.079 --> 00:48.212
If you don't recover the money

00:48.247 --> 00:50.380
that Anthony Mazlo
embezzled from us,

00:50.415 --> 00:52.216
every one of these
projects goes dark.

00:52.250 --> 00:53.951
Unless you got
a spare room or two

00:53.985 --> 00:55.919
for a couple thousand families
in your condo.

00:55.953 --> 00:57.754
I'm not really
a roommate kind of guy.

00:57.788 --> 00:58.854
Oh.

00:58.889 --> 01:00.489
Harvey's deposing
Elliot Perkins,

01:00.524 --> 01:02.424
Mazlo's number two,
this afternoon.

01:02.458 --> 01:04.058
Perkins had to have
knowledge of this,

01:04.093 --> 01:05.492
and he's going
to give up his boss.

01:05.528 --> 01:07.197
That's a promise.
Excuse me.

01:15.411 --> 01:18.781
Check it out.
Mazlo spent $500 a night

01:18.815 --> 01:21.620
on doggie daycare
on his trip to Greece.

01:21.654 --> 01:23.989
Greece.

01:24.024 --> 01:24.990
What?

01:25.025 --> 01:28.062
- Oh, nothing.
- Tell me.

01:28.097 --> 01:31.968
My first time
was in Greece.

01:32.002 --> 01:33.837
My God, you're picturing that
right now, aren't you?

01:33.871 --> 01:36.141
I have no choice.
I'm a visual person.

01:40.814 --> 01:42.349
You two
are really adorable.

01:42.383 --> 01:44.518
We're 48 hours from trial,
and you're gossiping

01:44.552 --> 01:46.954
like two 12-year-olds
at sleepaway camp.

01:51.961 --> 01:53.729
Listen up.

01:53.764 --> 01:56.433
Lucille Jackson's not just the
head of Stable Shelters, okay?

01:56.467 --> 01:58.503
She also sits
on the Board of Directors

01:58.537 --> 02:00.038
of several of
our largest clients.

02:00.072 --> 02:02.073
So if we lose this case,

02:02.107 --> 02:04.476
I doubt that her generosity's
going to extend to us.

02:04.511 --> 02:06.044
I would--
In my office.

02:06.079 --> 02:07.746
Bring the clarity-drilling IPO.

02:07.780 --> 02:11.149
Jerome Jensen's here.
Come on.

02:11.183 --> 02:13.151
Lucille's case
is all hands on deck, Harvey.

02:13.185 --> 02:15.319
You can't just--
I can, and I am.

02:15.354 --> 02:16.921
I thought we're
working on this together.

02:16.955 --> 02:18.155
Yeah, we are, Louis.

02:18.190 --> 02:20.458
Same way a golfer
and his caddy work together.

02:20.492 --> 02:22.926
Be that as it may,

02:22.961 --> 02:25.429
we are deposing Elliot Perkins
in 15 minutes, so--

02:25.463 --> 02:26.431
Perkins can wait.

02:26.465 --> 02:27.832
Just make sure that my 9 iron

02:27.867 --> 02:29.367
is nice and shiny
when I get there.

02:29.402 --> 02:31.570
Okay?
Come on, Mike.

02:35.776 --> 02:37.077
Harvey.

02:37.112 --> 02:39.213
Jerome Jensen,
meet Mike Ross.

02:39.247 --> 02:40.381
He's got the latest
on the IPO.

02:40.415 --> 02:41.715
- Hello, Mike.
- Mr. Jensen.

02:41.750 --> 02:44.185
I'm not here to talk
about my business, Harvey.

02:44.219 --> 02:47.388
Looks like my daughter might be
getting into some trouble.

02:47.422 --> 02:49.490
Mildred Wisnewski.

02:49.525 --> 02:51.692
What's Lola doing
with a fake I.D.?

02:51.727 --> 02:53.895
Well, that's what I hope
you can find out.

02:53.929 --> 02:55.363
It slipped out of her purse

02:55.397 --> 02:57.531
when she was ordering a drink
at a friend's bar mitzvah.

02:57.566 --> 03:01.268
Any idea what it's about?

03:01.303 --> 03:05.639
My relationship with Lola's
been rocky for a few years.

03:05.673 --> 03:08.876
If I asked her,
she'd just lie.

03:08.911 --> 03:10.178
Truth is,
I don't need to know.

03:10.213 --> 03:13.248
I just need you
to take care of it.

03:13.283 --> 03:16.152
Thank you.

03:16.186 --> 03:17.820
What the hell
is Harvey doing?

03:17.855 --> 03:19.622
He's supposed to be
deposing Elliot Perkins.

03:19.657 --> 03:20.723
He's with a client.

03:20.758 --> 03:22.726
I don't care.
We have a deposition.

03:22.760 --> 03:27.497
Don't even try it, Louis.

03:27.531 --> 03:28.831
I'm sorry.

03:28.866 --> 03:30.600
Let's--let's just start over.
Okay?

03:30.635 --> 03:32.936
Hi, Donna.
Hi.

03:32.970 --> 03:35.205
You know I like you,
right?

03:35.239 --> 03:36.807
But in the firm's food chain,

03:36.841 --> 03:39.976
I am a humpback whale,
and you are phytoplankton.

03:43.848 --> 03:46.316
June 3, 1997.

03:52.023 --> 03:53.724
That date
means nothing to me.

03:53.759 --> 03:56.661
Doesn't it?

03:56.695 --> 03:57.695
Who told you?

03:57.730 --> 03:59.497
Is the important thing
how I know

03:59.532 --> 04:01.432
or <i>that</i> I know?

04:01.467 --> 04:02.767
Does Harvey know?

04:02.801 --> 04:04.102
He can.

04:04.136 --> 04:05.403
I'm going to pay you.

04:05.438 --> 04:07.339
I just don't have
cash on me right now.

04:07.373 --> 04:09.108
So I'm gonna just tell Norma

04:09.142 --> 04:10.476
to run her old ass
out to the ATM

04:10.510 --> 04:12.411
and then bring it back
in a jiff, all right?

04:12.446 --> 04:13.546
I don't want your money,
Louis.

04:13.581 --> 04:14.547
I just want you to--

04:14.582 --> 04:16.683
I was not here.
I was not here.

04:16.716 --> 04:20.221
I was not here.

04:20.255 --> 04:21.656
All right,
let's get started, shall we?

04:21.690 --> 04:24.058
Isn't Harvey Specter
leading this deposition?

04:24.093 --> 04:26.460
He sent me.

04:26.495 --> 04:28.729
Now, Mr. Perkins,

04:28.764 --> 04:31.665
my first question to you is...

04:31.700 --> 04:35.003
Do you sleep well at night?

04:35.037 --> 04:36.571
Of course you do,

04:36.605 --> 04:39.608
'cause you have a roof
and a bed and running water,

04:39.642 --> 04:41.577
and by contrast,
thousands of families

04:41.611 --> 04:43.011
are gonna be sleeping
on the street

04:43.046 --> 04:45.414
when Stable Shelters is forced
to suspend their operations,

04:45.448 --> 04:48.050
all because of the money
that you stole.

04:48.084 --> 04:49.352
I never stole anything.

04:49.386 --> 04:50.453
You're Mazlo's number two.

04:50.487 --> 04:52.388
Money was embezzled.
Do you deny that?

04:52.422 --> 04:53.923
- Absolutely.
- Please, Robert,

04:53.957 --> 04:56.258
I know as general counsel
you just basically push paper,

04:56.293 --> 04:58.828
but please warn Mr. Perkins
about the penalties of perjury.

04:58.862 --> 05:00.930
Look, I'm not aware
of any perjury.

05:00.964 --> 05:02.498
We know about your account
in the Caymans.

05:02.533 --> 05:04.233
$20 million.
Are you kidding me?

05:04.268 --> 05:06.268
That transaction
was legitimate.

05:06.303 --> 05:08.504
Oh, when I take this public,
you're gonna be disgraced.

05:08.538 --> 05:12.174
Your wife, your children,
your whole family, disgraced.

05:12.209 --> 05:13.776
Would you show my client
some respect--

05:13.810 --> 05:16.345
And that transaction
had nothing to do with the firm.

05:16.380 --> 05:17.413
Bullshit.

05:17.447 --> 05:18.914
You either
took your cut from Mazlo,

05:18.949 --> 05:20.215
or it was hush money.

05:20.249 --> 05:21.382
Either way,
you're gonna live

05:21.417 --> 05:22.684
the rest of your life
as a pariah,

05:22.718 --> 05:24.052
or you give up Mazlo now.

05:24.086 --> 05:25.653
Is this a deposition
or an inquisition?

05:25.687 --> 05:27.855
This is ridiculous.
I can show you the records.

05:27.890 --> 05:29.857
Oh, sure you can.
Because you're the guy

05:29.892 --> 05:31.792
who invented losses
in mortgage-backed securities

05:31.827 --> 05:33.528
when you never even
bought them.

05:33.562 --> 05:35.329
I had no part in that.

05:35.364 --> 05:37.599
But you were aware of it,
and you did nothing about it.

05:37.633 --> 05:39.333
Come on, Louis.

05:39.368 --> 05:40.735
Can I get
a glass of water, please?

05:40.769 --> 05:43.738
You can't get any water.
We don't have any.

05:43.772 --> 05:45.973
You give up Mazlo now,
and this all stops.

05:46.008 --> 05:47.308
All right, that's--
that's it.

05:47.342 --> 05:48.309
My client needs a break.

05:48.343 --> 05:50.077
We can continue this
in ten minutes.

05:50.111 --> 05:54.214
I'm just getting started.

05:54.248 --> 05:55.949
I don't get it.
She looks so sweet.

05:55.983 --> 05:57.617
Don't let the photo
fool you.

05:57.651 --> 05:58.818
She's less "Girl Next Door"

05:58.852 --> 06:00.553
and more
"Girl with the Dragon Tattoo."

06:00.587 --> 06:01.787
Mm.

06:01.822 --> 06:03.856
Look, my plate's full
with Stable Shelters.

06:03.890 --> 06:05.791
I need you to look
into Jerome's daughter.

06:05.825 --> 06:08.060
Why didn't you just
hire a private investigator?

06:08.095 --> 06:09.262
Because if there's a problem,

06:09.296 --> 06:11.064
an investigator
can't fix it.

06:11.098 --> 06:13.300
I'm not just a lawyer
to Jerome, okay?

06:13.334 --> 06:17.405
I'm--I'm more like
Robert Duvall in <i>The Godfather.</i>

06:17.439 --> 06:19.374
His consigliere.

06:19.408 --> 06:21.576
Okay.

06:21.611 --> 06:22.644
What?

06:22.678 --> 06:24.180
Uh, nothing.

06:24.214 --> 06:26.415
Just if you're
his Robert Duvall,

06:26.449 --> 06:27.649
you're coming to me,

06:27.684 --> 06:29.918
so technically
I'm your Robert Duvall.

06:29.952 --> 06:32.688
You're my Fredo.

06:32.722 --> 06:35.991
Fredo?
No.

06:40.062 --> 06:42.597
Robert, what the hell
happened to Perkins?

06:42.631 --> 06:47.469
Ask that pit bull of yours.

06:47.503 --> 06:48.904
Uh, oh, no, actually.

06:48.938 --> 06:51.573
I prefer a female masseuse?

06:51.608 --> 06:53.275
If that--
can I call you right back?

06:53.310 --> 06:54.910
Right back.
Okay, bye.

06:54.945 --> 06:57.614
Perkins just got
wheeled out on stretcher.

06:57.648 --> 06:59.049
Well, he couldn't
handle the heat.

06:59.083 --> 07:00.050
He's probably faking it.

07:00.084 --> 07:01.051
What were you thinking,

07:01.085 --> 07:03.554
starting that deposition
without me?

07:03.588 --> 07:05.389
I don't know. Maybe if
you were doing your jo--

07:05.423 --> 07:07.224
- Oh, no.
- What?

07:07.258 --> 07:09.793
It's from Geller.
Perkins wasn't faking anything.

07:09.827 --> 07:12.569
Our best chance
to nail Anthony Mazlo's dead.

07:12.594 --> 07:15.594
